This project demonstrates a dynamic hybrid cryptographic communication system using RSA and AES algorithms, simulating secure data exchange such as drone command transmission. The program dynamically generates RSA key pairs at runtime, derives a random AES session key, encrypts user-provided messages and drone signals using AES-CBC, and securely exchanges the AES key using RSA-OAEP. Generated RSA keys are displayed and stored in a text file for inspection, and encrypted data is decrypted to verify integrity. The implementation showcases practical hybrid encryption, runtime parameterization (payloads and key size), and secure key handling suitable for educational or secure communication system demonstrations.
